This paper deals with fair machine learning and domain adaptation, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The paper also discusses the task of diagnosing acute kidney injury, which falls under the category of clinical informatics (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of measurement policy shift and selection bias, which are topics that are relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV).
